title: For Sale:  Arsenal SLR 106UR
postcontent:
This 5.56x45 rifle, now discontinued by Arsenal, has been converted by Definitive Arms of St. Petersburg, Florida to accept inexpensive and commonly available AR magazines. The conversion mag well is CNC machined steel, and is permanently installed. It incorporates a last-round bolt hold-open feature that is integral to the mag well, rather than relying on a protrusion on the mag follower, so the bolt remains open after the empty mag is withdrawn.
Additional upgrades to this rifle include: a Bulgarian next generation hinged top cover, which has a two-position flip rear sight (peep and notch) that is further back on the top cover than the factory sight for a longer sight radius; an Ultimak M13 railed optic mount that replaces the factory gas tube; and the 16.25" hammer forged chrome lined barrel has been threaded 1/2" x 28 RH and a birdcage flash hider installed. Finally, the feed ramp has been recontoured and polished to insure reliability with virtually any magazine or ammunition type. All work was done by Definitive Arms, and the rifle was tested exhaustively before it was returned to me.
The extension of the gas block / front sight combo is factory threaded 24mm RH, and includes a thread protector, so once you obtain the appropriate $200 tax stamp from ATF, the barrel can be cut and crowned at the front face of the threaded extension, and a 24mm RH muzzle device installed, and you'll have a 5.56 Krinkov that's much easier and better looking than converting a 106UR pistol by bolting an aftermarket folding stock to the rear trunion.
The rifle comes as pictured, other than the safety lever (it will come with the factory safety lever, and not the Krebs Custom lever shown.) It has a Magpul AK MOE pistol grip, and a US made, Arsenal marked polymer folding stock installed, but also comes with the factory triangle side folder. Also included, but not shown, are the factory gas tube with upper handguard, factory pistol grip, one 20 round PMag, and a Manticore Arms 24 mm RH NightBrake compensator, which will fit the threaded front sight base extension once the barrel is cut down (only after acquiring the required tax stamp.)
TERMS: The entire package is priced at $1,650.00, firm, FTF in northwest Hillsborough / west Pasco Counties, or shipped to your FFL. If FTF, buyer must show FL DL and FL CWL, and sign Bill of Sale. NO TRADES.

title: For Sale:  Black Aces Tactical Mossberg 500 12ga HD kit build will ship
postcontent: This was a build completely from the ground up. Started as a Maverick 88 style receiver from Black Aces Tactical (cross bolt safety is easier to use with a pistol grip then Mossberg OEM style). The kit itself came with a new bolt and firing pin. The rest of the internals are all Mossberg OEM parts and the barrel is of a SPX 18.5" model with a fiber optic sight that has been converted to function with the new feeding system. Whole gun was inspected and ok'ed by a professional gunsmith. Has only shot less then 100 rounds. This build does not offer the "SpringBok" system since it was a parts kit build.  Externally the action tube is a 6 3/4 tube with extended nut with a fitted Magpul M-Lok hand guard. The rail and sight are UTG made, the sight is fully adjustable. The stock is an Ergo adapter with a milspec pistol grip and and commercial tube and butstock with a limbsaver pad. The tube has been bored out to remove the assembly with out complete disassembly of the entire rear unit.  Comes with a converted saiga 5rd magazine with the kits original parts (follower and feed lip clip) and also a used drum mag feed ramp that was pinned to a 10 rounder (not included).  As is the gun fires on every shot chambered, the issue is the current magazine needs more tuning and work. It only works part of the time and malfunctions the rest. Black Aces Tactical Sells there in house own made mags that offer 100% performance and reliability. The action is a tad bit on the heavy side and still needs to be worn in and or lightly polished.  I'm selling this as is with everything you see in the picture plus the feed ramp. I have way too many irons in the fire at the moment and don't feel like investing in the magazines and rounding out the edges. Great working gun just needs the mags to make it run 100%. Asking for $400. Must go through FFL. will ship to your FFL on your dime, buyer is responsible for all fees and I will not part out the gun now or anytime soon.  Not looking for any trades or partial trades.

title: For Sale:  Dan Wesson 357mag EARLY MODEL  Monson
postcontent: I've got Dan Wesson early 14-2 357 that I am selling.  It's hard to date exactly but I do know it was made between 1968 and 1975 as it is a Monson model with a "pork chop" shroud.  So say these models are more desirable but I have no opinon one way or another.  It's just a damn fine shooting gun and that's all that matters to me.If you don't know the Dan Wesson story, I'd invite you to do some research, the pistol had some really interesting design features that I couldn't do justice if I tried to explain them.  You'll soon see why people like collecting them.The bluing is worn in places and the grips have been replaced however it locks up very tight, the cylindar gap is tiny and the rifling is amazing, especially so for a 40+ year old gun.  It shoots like a dream.  It has the best double action trigger pull of any revolver I've ever shot let alone owned.  The trigger pull on this would put any S&W I've encountered (whose triggers I love) to shame.  The single action trigger is great too.  It's very, very light which may be good or bad depending on your preference.This particular gun is very accurate too and not all of them were.  The sights on the model 14 aren't adjustable but that isn't a problem with this one.  I'm not a great shot, especially not with revolvers but I can hit orange sized targets at 12 yards with Double Action fire.  I can't do that with any other revolver I have.  I really hate to sell this but I really could use the money for something else.  If you're really nice and don't beat me up on price I'll throw in a holster and your choice of a box of either 38spl SJHPs or a box of .357 JSP.This is a good deal on a great pistol with some innovative features that you cant find anymore.
